|><| 𝐁𝐫𝐞𝐚𝐤 & 𝐂𝐨𝐧𝐭𝐢𝐧𝐮𝐞 𝐒𝐭𝐚𝐭𝐞𝐦𝐞𝐧𝐭 |><|
       <><><>><><><><><><><>

 𝟏. 𝐁𝐫𝐞𝐚𝐤 𝐒𝐭𝐚𝐭𝐞𝐦𝐞𝐧𝐭 :::---
     >> The break statement is used to terminate the loop immediately.

   For Example ;;;
     for i in range(10):
     if i == 5:
        break
        print(i)  # Stops when i is 5

 𝟐. 𝐂𝐨𝐧𝐭𝐢𝐧𝐮𝐞 𝐒𝐭𝐚𝐭𝐞𝐦𝐞𝐧𝐭  :::---
     >> The continue statement is used to skip the current iteration of the loop it continue with next.

   For Example ;;;
     for i in range(5):
     if i == 2:
        continue
        print(i)  # Skips 2

-------------------><----------------------><---------------------

|><| 𝐞𝐥𝐬𝐞 𝐰𝐢𝐭𝐡 𝐋𝐨𝐨𝐩𝐬 |><|
      >> Executes if the loop completes normally.

   For Example ;;;
    for i in range(5):
      print(i)
    else:
      print("Loop completed!")

------------------><--------------------><-----------------------
